<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[332,1263,392,1737]" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">
Specimens were intercepted on privet on a very few occasions, and only as adults. Therefore we suspect it does not reproduce on privet. The species has a wide distribution in South America, like 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[900,1064,1069,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Acrosternum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impicticorne">
<emphasis box="[900,1064,1069,1092]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">A. impicticorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from Colombia to Argentina (ROLSTON, 1983). In Brazil it is reported from State of Rio Grande do Sul (
<bibRefCitation author="LINK, D. &amp; GRAZIA, J." box="[339,570,1126,1150]" journalOrPublisher="Anais Soc. ent. Brasil, Porto Alegre" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" pagination="115 - 129" part="16" refId="ref6423" refString="LINK, D. &amp; GRAZIA, J. 1987. Pentatomideos da regiao central do Rio Grande do Sul. Anais Soc. ent. Brasil, Porto Alegre, 16 (1): 115 - 129." title="Pentatomideos da regiao central do Rio Grande do Sul" type="journal article" year="1987">LINK &amp; GRAZIA, 1987</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record for Paraná.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[332,1263,392,1737]" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">Adults with dorsal surface of the body green and densely puncturated, with margins of head, thorax and abdomen orange yellow; legs green. Median body length of females 18.5 mm (n = 5), and of males 16.2 mm (n = 5). Nonymphs and eggs were observed on privet plants.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
